            . On the 28th of January, about half-past nine o'clock in the morning, on arriving at our ware-house, I was informed of this robbery, and found the prisoner in custody with the cotton.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-59-person565">
                  JOHN 
                  GIBSON
               <interp inst="t18320216-59-person565" type="surname" value="GIBSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-59-person565" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320216-59-person565" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am porter to the prosecutors. About half-past seven o'clock in the morning, just as the warehouse was open, I saw the prisoner take this cotton, which was near the door - there were two other servants in the warehouse, but they were at the back part; I was about seven yards from the door - my back was towards the prisoner when he came in, but my face was to him when he took it; he went out with it - I went after him, overtook him with the print on his shoulder, and brought him back; he had five pieces of cotton.</p>
               <p>
            
